is decade, the author enhances its context through a story about his own personal belongings. Examining popular genres including television, film, music, fashion, disco and city magazine, this book teases out the distinctive aspects of Hong Kong pop culture that defined (his) Hong Kong. As Hong Kong has been undergoing drastic changes in recent years, it is necessary to point toward new imaginaries by re-examining its development. Toward this end, this book will shed light on an important research area of Hong Kong Studies as an academic discipline.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPopular culturezChinazHong KongxHistoryy20th century. 4aAsian Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aUrban Cultures. 7aART / Art & Politics.2bisacsh  aHong Kong cinema, Cantopop, cosmopolitanism, hybridities.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048555000?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048555000423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048555000/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles